**[P2] Performance concern: No image lazy loading specified for blog posts** (confidence: 6/10)

Plan says "Images: Store in `public/blog/images/`, optimize with `next/image`" but doesn't specify lazy loading strategy.

**Problem**: Blog post with 10 images loads all 10 immediately, even those below the fold. Wastes bandwidth, slows initial render.

**Recommendation**: Use `next/image` with `loading="lazy"` for below-fold images:

```tsx
// components/BlogPost.tsx
import Image from 'next/image'

export function BlogPost({ images }) {
  return (
    <article>
      <Image 
        src={images[0]} 
        loading="eager"  // Hero image loads immediately
        priority
      />
      {images.slice(1).map(img => (
        <Image 
          key={img.src}
          src={img.src}
          loading="lazy"  // Below-fold images lazy load
        />
      ))}
    </article>
  )
}
```

This loads first image immediately, defers rest until viewport. Saves bandwidth on long posts.

