**[P2] Performance concern: No caching strategy specified for RSS** (confidence: 5/10)

Plan mentions RSS generation but no caching. Every deploy regenerates RSS even if no blog posts changed.

**Problem**: Wasted build time. CI/CD runs RSS generation on every deploy, even for CSS-only changes.

**Recommendation**: Add cache invalidation logic to RSS generation script:

```javascript
// scripts/generate-rss.js
const fs = require('fs')
const path = require('path')
const matter = require('gray-matter')
const RSS = require('rss')

const BLOG_DIR = 'content/blog'
const RSS_OUTPUT = 'public/rss.xml'
const CACHE_FILE = '.cache/blog-posts.json'

// Check cache
const cache = fs.existsSync(CACHE_FILE) ? JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(CACHE_FILE, 'utf8')) : { posts: [] }
const currentPosts = fs.readdirSync(BLOG_DIR).filter(f => f.endsWith('.mdx'))

// Skip generation if no changes
if (JSON.stringify(currentPosts.sort()) === JSON.stringify(cache.posts.sort())) {
  console.log('No blog changes detected, skipping RSS generation')
  process.exit(0)
}

// Generate RSS...
// ...

// Update cache
fs.writeFileSync(CACHE_FILE, JSON.stringify({ posts: currentPosts }))
```

This skips RSS generation on no-op deploys, saving build time.

Good - cache invalidation is the right call for efficiency.

**[P1] Performance concern: No memory limit specified for WebGL scene** (confidence: 7/10)

Plan sets performance budgets (frame time, draw calls) but no memory budget. WebGL scenes can leak memory (geometries, textures, shaders) if not disposed properly.

**Problem**: Long session with portfolio open → memory grows → browser tab crashes or garbage collection pauses.

**Recommendation**: Add memory budget to performance monitoring:

```javascript
// utils/performance.js
const MEMORY_BUDGET = 100 * 1024 * 1024 // 100MB

export function checkMemoryLimit() {
  if (performance.memory) {
    const used = performance.memory.usedJSHeapSize
    if (used > MEMORY_BUDGET) {
      console.warn(`Memory budget exceeded: ${(used / 1024 / 1024).toFixed(0)}MB used`)
      // Could trigger particle disable here too
      return { shouldReduceComplexity: true }
    }
  }
  return { shouldReduceComplexity: false }
}
```

Also add `useEffect` cleanup in all R3F components to dispose geometries/materials.

